WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.126 --> 00:00:02.920
<i>Previously on</i> Foundation...

2
00:00:03.003 --> 00:00:05.714
The Second Foundation must be kept secret.

3
00:00:05.797 --> 00:00:07.716
<i>I am done being used.</i>

4
00:00:07.799 --> 00:00:09.039
- Stop! Stop! Stop!
- I don't...

5
00:00:10.802 --> 00:00:12.947
We're transferring
your nanobots into my blood.

6
00:00:12.971 --> 00:00:14.598
I'm going to go back to the palace.

7
00:00:14.681 --> 00:00:16.058
and I'm gonna be you.

8
00:00:18.310 --> 00:00:19.603
Brother Day will be home soon.

9
00:00:19.686 --> 00:00:21.104
You can plead your case to him.

10
00:00:21.688 --> 00:00:24.024
We can share the <i>Invictus</i>.
We can repair it.

11
00:00:27.778 --> 00:00:29.279
Freestone. wait!

12
00:00:29.363 --> 00:00:30.697
Well. this is encouraging.

13
00:00:30.781 --> 00:00:33.450
Seeing you all gathered here
gives me hope.

14
00:00:33.534 --> 00:00:35.285
We might actually pull this off.

15
00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:43.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

16
00:00:51.107 --> 00:00:55.778
<i>My mother used to say
that going to sleep was a leap of faith.</i>

17
00:00:58.615 --> 00:01:02.577
<i>Our souls wander when we dream.
or so she told me.</i>

18
00:01:07.332 --> 00:01:09.459
<i>And if we say our devotions.</i>

19
00:01:10.543 --> 00:01:13.713
<i>our souls will find their way back
before we wake.</i>

20
00:01:18.134 --> 00:01:20.845
<i>Climbing from our cradle is another leap.</i>

21
00:01:22.680 --> 00:01:24.599
<i>So is leaving the comfort of home.</i>

22
00:01:28.228 --> 00:01:33.149
<i>For some. it's setting sail.
hurtling ourselves into the void.</i>

23
00:01:35.235 --> 00:01:40.656
<i>We send messages into space
hoping someone will answer.</i>

24
00:01:41.783 --> 00:01:45.954
<i>praying we find safe harbor
over the horizon.</i>

25
00:02:12.313 --> 00:02:14.607
Anacreon and Thespis.

26
00:02:14.691 --> 00:02:17.652
you've been at each other's throats
so long.

27
00:02:18.319 --> 00:02:22.031
the origin of your enmity is
almost irrelevant.

28
00:02:22.615 --> 00:02:24.576
We have legitimate grounds for our hatred.

29
00:02:24.659 --> 00:02:27.829
The First Betrayal
and a thousand atrocities since.

30
00:02:27.912 --> 00:02:29.914
No one knows
what really happened that night.

31
00:02:31.624 --> 00:02:33.167
The First Betrayal.

32
00:02:33.751 --> 00:02:38.131
A Thespin king newly wed
to an Anacreon huntress.

33
00:02:39.090 --> 00:02:42.969
The two emerging powers
of the Outer Reach united in marriage.

34
00:02:43.052 --> 00:02:45.554
Are you gonna teach us
our own history now. dead man? Huh?

35
00:02:45.637 --> 00:02:48.099
The Thespin dog slit her throat
on their wedding bed.

36
00:02:48.892 --> 00:02:50.268
So the legend goes.

37
00:02:50.351 --> 00:02:52.562
Are you suggesting our history's wrong?

38
00:02:52.645 --> 00:02:58.234
History is written by the victor.
and neither of you seem to be winning.

39
00:02:58.318 --> 00:02:59.777
There was a witness.

40
00:02:59.861 --> 00:03:03.072
The only witness.
an Anacreon handmaid who testified

41
00:03:03.156 --> 00:03:06.576
that King Throy un Thark got drunk
the night of the wedding

42
00:03:07.368 --> 00:03:11.080
and. in a fit of rage.
murdered your huntress.

43
00:03:11.164 --> 00:03:12.874
The handmaid lied.

44
00:03:12.957 --> 00:03:15.543
The nature of the lie is relevant here.

45
00:03:16.419 --> 00:03:19.881
On her deathbed.
the handmaid made a confession.

46
00:03:20.590 --> 00:03:24.427
The real murderer was Cleon II.

47
00:03:25.011 --> 00:03:27.972
The first clone
in the Genetic Dynasty realized

48
00:03:28.056 --> 00:03:31.142
that a plan could unfold
over several lifetimes.

49
00:03:31.226 --> 00:03:33.561
He saw where this new alliance could lead.

50
00:03:33.645 --> 00:03:39.692
so he had his shadowmaster seduce
the handmaiden. drug the newlyweds.

51
00:03:39.776 --> 00:03:43.363
murder your huntress
and implicate your king.

52
00:03:44.030 --> 00:03:46.491
Why fight two upstart kingdoms

53
00:03:46.574 --> 00:03:51.329
when you can exploit their racial animus
and have them fight each other?

54
00:03:53.081 --> 00:03:54.916
The clones played you.

55
00:03:55.792 --> 00:03:59.128
But today. thanks to the Foundation.

56
00:03:59.629 --> 00:04:03.800
we could put back together
what Empire has broken.

57
00:04:03.883 --> 00:04:08.471
No. We are not uniting with them now.
no matter how this started.

58
00:04:08.555 --> 00:04:11.558
And even if we did. Empire is too strong.

59
00:04:11.641 --> 00:04:13.309
Now you have the <i>Invictus</i>.

60
00:04:13.393 --> 00:04:15.520
The <i>Invictus</i> is only one ship.

61
00:04:15.603 --> 00:04:18.106
One ship can be the first of many.

62
00:04:18.189 --> 00:04:23.027
If both your peoples will set aside hatred
in favor of strength.

63
00:04:23.653 --> 00:04:25.363
as those poor newlyweds did.

64
00:04:25.446 --> 00:04:30.410
then you'll find here
the skills necessary to build more ships.

65
00:04:31.035 --> 00:04:34.581
For the Plan to succeed.
the Foundation needs three pillars.

66
00:04:34.664 --> 00:04:37.417
just as a stool needs three legs.

67
00:04:37.500 --> 00:04:40.003
It needs all the children
of the Outer Reach.

68
00:04:40.086 --> 00:04:41.588
That is the way I designed it.

69
00:04:41.671 --> 00:04:45.550
So. Hari. you knew
the <i>Invictus</i> would be discovered?

70
00:04:46.050 --> 00:04:49.804
Hello. Mari. Good to see you again.

71
00:04:51.764 --> 00:04:52.848
Where's Gaal?

72
00:04:52.932 --> 00:04:54.766
She never made it to Terminus.

73
00:04:55.935 --> 00:04:57.270
And you are?

74
00:04:59.230 --> 00:05:00.315
Salvor Hardin.

75
00:05:01.524 --> 00:05:02.609
Mari's daughter.

76
00:05:03.860 --> 00:05:05.737
I'm the one who opened the Vault

77
00:05:05.820 --> 00:05:08.323
and who wrestled that damn ship
onto our doorstep.

78
00:05:08.823 --> 00:05:13.161
Well. Salvor Hardin.
it appears thanks are in order.

79
00:05:13.828 --> 00:05:16.289
As to the mystery of the <i>Invictus</i>.

80
00:05:16.372 --> 00:05:19.876
its appearances were one of the first
tests I gave my predictive models.

81
00:05:20.376 --> 00:05:24.797
Where others saw chaos. I found a pattern.

82
00:05:25.423 --> 00:05:29.093
I don't understand.
We're not revolutionaries.

83
00:05:29.177 --> 00:05:30.762
You said so yourself at the trial.

84
00:05:31.346 --> 00:05:33.723
Well. I might have lied about that.

85
00:05:52.533 --> 00:05:54.619
I am grateful. Brother Dusk.

86
00:05:54.702 --> 00:05:58.373
That I saved our dynasty
from infiltration?

87
00:05:58.456 --> 00:06:02.919
I wonder. Day. if you'd stayed on Trantor
and not traveled to the Maiden.

88
00:06:03.711 --> 00:06:05.838
would you have apprehended
his differences?

89
00:06:07.173 --> 00:06:11.970
You and I are the same.
I have to believe I would have.

90
00:06:14.305 --> 00:06:17.308
The more important question is
what do we do now?

91
00:06:18.810 --> 00:06:20.520
You know what we have to do.

92
00:06:36.119 --> 00:06:37.120
Out.

93
00:06:42.208 --> 00:06:44.335
We're still unraveling
the exact methodology.

94
00:06:44.419 --> 00:06:48.548
but apparently they corrupted
your nanoparticle regimen some time ago.

95
00:06:49.716 --> 00:06:50.925
You're not one of us.

96
00:06:52.510 --> 00:06:55.138
Your DNA has been altered in a dozen ways.

97
00:06:55.638 --> 00:06:57.056
You look like us.

98
00:06:59.559 --> 00:07:01.269
You sound like us. but...

99
00:07:07.942 --> 00:07:09.694
How long have you known?

100
00:07:09.777 --> 00:07:11.154
That I'm different?

101
00:07:13.656 --> 00:07:15.825
I used to steal away
and watch holos of you...

102
00:07:18.202 --> 00:07:19.370
eating breakfast.

103
00:07:20.788 --> 00:07:22.248
sitting in the throne room.

104
00:07:22.749 --> 00:07:25.752
I counted how often you smiled
at your subjects.

105
00:07:26.419 --> 00:07:29.672
whether you sat
with your hands together or apart.

106
00:07:29.756 --> 00:07:31.841
how often you drank from your cup
at meals.

107
00:07:32.342 --> 00:07:34.594
I knew even then that I wasn't like you.

108
00:07:36.554 --> 00:07:37.805
But I wanted to be.

109
00:07:48.733 --> 00:07:49.984
What are you going to do?

110
00:07:50.068 --> 00:07:52.111
You conspired with insurgents.

111
00:07:52.195 --> 00:07:53.613
I wasn't conspiring.

112
00:07:53.696 --> 00:07:56.241
You trusted your secrets to our enemies
and fled the palace.

113
00:07:56.324 --> 00:07:58.724
- She tricked me!
- Because she had a foothold in your heart!

114
00:07:58.785 --> 00:08:00.411
And who created that foothold?

115
00:08:01.037 --> 00:08:02.038
Look at us!

116
00:08:02.622 --> 00:08:05.291
We have no mothers. no aunts. no uncles.

117
00:08:05.375 --> 00:08:06.876
We have sex with concubines

118
00:08:06.960 --> 00:08:09.170
whose memories are erased
the moment we leave them!

119
00:08:10.255 --> 00:08:12.382
Have you never longed to leave this place?

120
00:08:14.050 --> 00:08:17.887
Have you never felt stifled
by the weight of our ascendants?

121
00:08:19.681 --> 00:08:23.101
Can you truly say that
all you've ever wanted

122
00:08:23.184 --> 00:08:28.231
was to be an installment
in a long. long line of us.

123
00:08:29.691 --> 00:08:32.193
living out a script written centuries ago?

124
00:08:36.656 --> 00:08:39.951
All my life.
I've wanted to call you "Father."

125
00:08:41.077 --> 00:08:42.579
But you're not my father.

126
00:08:44.122 --> 00:08:45.957
We're not even people. Day.

127
00:08:47.500 --> 00:08:52.589
We're just... echoes of the first Cleon.

128
00:08:55.383 --> 00:08:58.595
So is a corrupted echo
more original than a perfect one?

129
00:09:00.763 --> 00:09:02.849
Or does it fade away to nothing?

130
00:09:11.441 --> 00:09:14.485
So the curation.
everything we've been doing here.

131
00:09:14.568 --> 00:09:15.736
has all been for nothing?

132
00:09:15.820 --> 00:09:17.614
Not for nothing. Mari.

133
00:09:18.197 --> 00:09:20.658
Your time here on Terminus
hasn't been wasted.

134
00:09:21.367 --> 00:09:23.328
It got you out
from under the Empire's grasp.

135
00:09:23.411 --> 00:09:24.412
It hardened you.

136
00:09:24.495 --> 00:09:28.541
But the Foundation was never
about curating knowledge.

137
00:09:30.418 --> 00:09:32.253
It was about curating people.

138
00:09:35.423 --> 00:09:37.967
You. the original settlers.

139
00:09:38.509 --> 00:09:43.598
you possess qualities vital in forming
the seeds of a new civilization.

140
00:09:44.349 --> 00:09:49.020
And you. Anacreons and Thespins.
you are the consummate survivors.

141
00:09:49.687 --> 00:09:52.732
Consigned to history
by the Empire and yet.

142
00:09:53.775 --> 00:09:56.986
together. you represent the future.

143
00:09:58.112 --> 00:10:01.366
The human race is an ever-evolving story

144
00:10:01.449 --> 00:10:05.912
told over thousands of years
by a countless number of voices.

145
00:10:07.205 --> 00:10:08.414
But for a long time now.

146
00:10:08.498 --> 00:10:12.627
that chorus has been
suffocated and quietly erased.

147
00:10:13.211 --> 00:10:17.548
Because under the Genetic Dynasty.
there is only room for one story.

148
00:10:17.632 --> 00:10:18.967
One voice.

149
00:10:19.050 --> 00:10:22.971
We cannot become who we must become
if the Empire is allowed to persist.

150
00:10:24.556 --> 00:10:27.934
That path leads to
the annihilation of the human race.

151
00:10:28.643 --> 00:10:33.606
Even if we embrace this destiny of yours.
the Empire will be here within weeks.

152
00:10:33.690 --> 00:10:37.151
He's right. They were already
investigating the comms buoy.

153
00:10:37.235 --> 00:10:39.862
It's only a matter of time
before they send reinforcements.

154
00:10:39.946 --> 00:10:45.201
The Empire won't come. Not yet.
Not if they think you're already dead.

155
00:10:45.702 --> 00:10:48.997
Take the <i>Invictus</i>
to the far side of your star.

156
00:10:49.080 --> 00:10:53.751
activate the quantum drive.
but maintain your position in subspace...

157
00:10:53.835 --> 00:10:56.212
The energy signature would read
as a mega-flare.

158
00:10:57.714 --> 00:10:59.714
A mega-flare would wipe out
all life in the system.

159
00:10:59.757 --> 00:11:02.927
The Empire comprises
tens of thousands of worlds.

160
00:11:03.011 --> 00:11:06.264
A dangerous star with dead planets
in a distant arm of the galaxy

161
00:11:06.347 --> 00:11:10.518
won't merit further investigation
even if it did once host the Foundation.

162
00:11:11.227 --> 00:11:13.688
It could work. It could.

163
00:11:14.188 --> 00:11:16.399
As long as don't we stray
beyond the Outer Reach.

164
00:11:17.400 --> 00:11:18.776
we'd be invisible to them.

165
00:11:18.860 --> 00:11:20.028
We'd be free.

166
00:11:20.111 --> 00:11:21.404
You'd be free.

167
00:11:22.238 --> 00:11:26.492
to bide your time. to build.
to become who you need to become.

168
00:11:28.411 --> 00:11:30.121
So. are you the ghost then?

169
00:11:31.372 --> 00:11:32.582
I suppose I am.

170
00:11:32.665 --> 00:11:34.334
- What's it like to die?
- Keir.

171
00:11:34.417 --> 00:11:35.668
What? I want to know.

172
00:11:39.130 --> 00:11:40.423
Did you see anything?

173
00:11:42.133 --> 00:11:44.260
Those are complex questions.

174
00:11:44.344 --> 00:11:48.139
Then answer a simple one.
How'd you get here?

175
00:11:49.098 --> 00:11:50.558
What's your name. son?

176
00:11:50.642 --> 00:11:53.061
Poly. Poly Verisof.

177
00:11:53.144 --> 00:11:57.315
Well. Poly Verisof.
shortly before I died.

178
00:11:57.982 --> 00:12:03.321
I swallowed a pill containing millions
of self-replicating molecular machines.

179
00:12:04.030 --> 00:12:08.034
As per my mortality directive.
my casket was jettisoned out into space.

180
00:12:08.826 --> 00:12:11.663
<i>Those machines began breaking down
my body tissue</i>

181
00:12:11.746 --> 00:12:14.290
<i>into all its constituent elements.</i>

182
00:12:14.374 --> 00:12:16.960
Then those machines recycled
those elements.

183
00:12:17.043 --> 00:12:20.713
scooping up more material. ice.
micrometeoroids. et cetera.

184
00:12:20.797 --> 00:12:23.549
assembling
the Vault's internal scaffolding.

185
00:12:24.217 --> 00:12:26.219
You're saying
the Vault isn't just your tomb?

186
00:12:27.387 --> 00:12:28.888
The Vault is you?

187
00:12:29.389 --> 00:12:32.392
You've been on Terminus this whole time.
watching us?

188
00:12:32.475 --> 00:12:37.105
No. It wouldn't have been wise for me
to have been sentient all this time.

189
00:12:37.188 --> 00:12:40.316
That kind of isolation can undo
even the strongest minds.

190
00:12:40.817 --> 00:12:44.946
No. the process of my awakening
was triggered by the Anacreons.

191
00:12:45.446 --> 00:12:46.906
When the null field expanded.

192
00:12:47.448 --> 00:12:50.201
It takes time
to rebuild consciousness. Salvor.

193
00:12:50.285 --> 00:12:53.413
The null field is just part of
the Vault's automatic defense system.

194
00:12:53.997 --> 00:12:55.582
Will we see you again?

195
00:12:55.665 --> 00:12:57.333
Oh. I expect so. Poly.

196
00:12:58.501 --> 00:13:02.797
This isn't the Foundation's first crisis.
and it won't be the last.

197
00:13:03.381 --> 00:13:07.385
You've bought a reprieve.
but war with Empire is inevitable.

198
00:13:08.177 --> 00:13:13.975
In the meantime. remember this day.
Remember what we're striving towards.

199
00:13:14.058 --> 00:13:17.312
I know a thousand years can seem
like an eternity.

200
00:13:17.812 --> 00:13:21.441
but it's the blink of an eye when measured
against the whole of human history.

201
00:13:21.524 --> 00:13:26.195
and it could so easily slip
through our fingers if we're not vigilant.

202
00:13:29.949 --> 00:13:33.411
No. wait! So. that's it?
That's all we get?

203
00:13:33.494 --> 00:13:35.163
I've given you what you need.

204
00:13:35.246 --> 00:13:37.916
What about the visions
you've been sending me?

205
00:13:37.999 --> 00:13:39.167
Visions?

206
00:13:39.250 --> 00:13:40.251
Yes.

207
00:13:40.752 --> 00:13:43.796
The ghost. You've been talking to me
since I was a kid.

208
00:13:43.880 --> 00:13:45.298
And... And I had these visions.

209
00:13:45.381 --> 00:13:47.634
I've seen you on Trantor.
on the slow ship.

210
00:13:48.593 --> 00:13:51.304
They guided me.
Y... You helped me solve the crisis.

211
00:13:52.639 --> 00:13:53.640
Curious.

212
00:13:55.683 --> 00:13:57.602
Well. Salvor Hardin.

213
00:13:58.978 --> 00:14:00.980
whatever messages you've been receiving.

214
00:14:01.064 --> 00:14:04.484
I assure you they haven't come from me.

215
00:15:28.109 --> 00:15:29.110
Walk with me.

216
00:15:34.115 --> 00:15:36.910
I know people hate me. consider me evil.

217
00:15:37.702 --> 00:15:39.370
But it is my detachment.

218
00:15:41.080 --> 00:15:42.790
my indifference to suffering.

219
00:15:43.374 --> 00:15:45.376
that allows me to rule effectively.

220
00:15:46.669 --> 00:15:48.963
The galaxy is so vast.

221
00:15:50.423 --> 00:15:52.342
the problems so large.

222
00:15:52.425 --> 00:15:55.428
that I must turn a blind eye
to the individual.

223
00:15:57.722 --> 00:15:58.723
Hmm.

224
00:15:59.265 --> 00:16:00.266
Look there.

225
00:16:02.518 --> 00:16:06.397
It's a strange burden
not being allowed to carry a burden.

226
00:16:08.399 --> 00:16:11.736
My brothers and I shift it
amongst ourselves because we're a family.

227
00:16:14.864 --> 00:16:17.825
And we love one another in our own way.

228
00:16:19.494 --> 00:16:21.496
I'm sure you find that hard to believe.

229
00:16:23.414 --> 00:16:26.334
Do you ever think
about your legacy. Azura?

230
00:16:28.127 --> 00:16:30.713
The mark you leave behind
after you're gone?

231
00:16:34.592 --> 00:16:38.680
As a child. I wanted to be better
than the Cleons who came before.

232
00:16:39.514 --> 00:16:45.186
Smarter. braver. more dazzling
in the justice I handed out.

233
00:16:48.898 --> 00:16:51.693
But as I matured. my aspirations evolved.

234
00:16:52.527 --> 00:16:54.779
I no longer wanted to be the best.

235
00:16:55.280 --> 00:17:00.743
I wanted to be the same.
Predictable courage. predictable justice.

236
00:17:00.827 --> 00:17:06.457
I wanted my son to be the same too.
Another Cleon. Perfectly Cleon.

237
00:17:06.541 --> 00:17:07.625
He's not your son.

238
00:17:11.087 --> 00:17:12.297
Of course he is.

239
00:17:16.593 --> 00:17:20.096
He is my brother. He is also my son.

240
00:17:22.056 --> 00:17:23.558
I rocked him as a baby.

241
00:17:24.559 --> 00:17:28.980
I cultivated him just as you've nurtured
the plants in this garden.

242
00:17:30.648 --> 00:17:33.192
It's a powerful thing. caring for a life.

243
00:17:35.194 --> 00:17:37.113
Why are you telling me all of this?

244
00:17:39.365 --> 00:17:41.701
Because of all the galaxy's citizens...

245
00:17:43.953 --> 00:17:48.290
you have the singular distinction
of having robbed me of my personal legacy.

246
00:17:49.291 --> 00:17:51.044
Which leads me to your legacy.

247
00:17:53.046 --> 00:17:56.341
I know you're not the architect
of this plot. but you are the face of it.

248
00:17:56.424 --> 00:17:58.885
The face that broke my son's heart.

249
00:18:00.595 --> 00:18:03.848
We traced your family tree
back to your great-great-grandparents.

250
00:18:03.932 --> 00:18:08.228
and then identified all living descendants
branching out from those 16 individuals.

251
00:18:08.853 --> 00:18:11.731
Not just direct descendants.
but all the aunts and uncles.

252
00:18:12.815 --> 00:18:15.735
first and second cousins.
removed or otherwise.

253
00:18:15.818 --> 00:18:17.737
Do you know how many people we uncovered?

254
00:18:18.696 --> 00:18:20.490
712.

255
00:18:22.408 --> 00:18:25.453
Then we located all your friends
and lovers. past and present.

256
00:18:25.536 --> 00:18:29.540
First boy you kissed. the young woman
you gave your virginity to.

257
00:18:30.959 --> 00:18:34.837
Your teachers and coworkers.
even those here on the palace grounds.

258
00:18:35.546 --> 00:18:40.843
We located their parents and siblings.
Basically. anyone in your extended orbit.

259
00:18:42.011 --> 00:18:45.765
That amounted to another 839 individuals.

260
00:18:46.266 --> 00:18:49.143
1.551 people.

261
00:18:51.020 --> 00:18:53.898
The sum total of lives you've made
a meaningful mark on.

262
00:18:54.857 --> 00:18:59.696
In short. the people who would
remember you after you're gone.

263
00:19:01.322 --> 00:19:02.407
Even as we speak.

264
00:19:02.490 --> 00:19:06.494
every member of your personal
constellation is under our surveillance.

265
00:19:06.578 --> 00:19:09.664
a particle beam targeting
each of their brain stems.

266
00:19:09.747 --> 00:19:13.918
At my signal.
they will all cease to exist.

267
00:19:19.299 --> 00:19:20.300
There.

268
00:19:21.384 --> 00:19:22.468
All gone.

269
00:19:24.679 --> 00:19:26.973
Your legacy has been erased. Azura.

270
00:19:28.016 --> 00:19:31.728
Whatever minute waves your being managed
to propagate throughout the universe

271
00:19:31.811 --> 00:19:33.354
have been canceled out.

272
00:19:37.191 --> 00:19:41.779
You will be placed in an automated cell
and fed intravenously.

273
00:19:42.405 --> 00:19:44.741
restrained so as to prevent self-harm.

274
00:19:45.617 --> 00:19:48.578
You will be sensory shrouded
for the rest of your life.

275
00:19:48.661 --> 00:19:53.750
You will never see. nor hear.
nor smell. nor taste. nor touch again.

276
00:19:55.418 --> 00:19:56.753
But you will be aware.

277
00:19:58.296 --> 00:20:01.841
And you will remember
what you have taken from me.

278
00:20:29.577 --> 00:20:30.703
Hari Seldon.

279
00:20:32.413 --> 00:20:37.543
seeing all this coming
and telling us nothing.

280
00:20:37.627 --> 00:20:39.587
I thought we'd be sitting out the fall.

281
00:20:40.463 --> 00:20:41.464
I thought our work

282
00:20:41.547 --> 00:20:44.926
was building a time capsule
some future survivors would open.

283
00:20:45.009 --> 00:20:47.409
I never imagined we'd be
the ones putting the Plan in action.

284
00:20:49.305 --> 00:20:51.432
Do you still believe
the Empire's gonna collapse?

285
00:20:53.017 --> 00:20:54.018
Yes.

286
00:20:54.811 --> 00:20:56.813
Do you still believe
humanity can do better?

287
00:20:57.397 --> 00:21:00.358
Of course I do.
No one sane wants the Empire to continue.

288
00:21:01.025 --> 00:21:02.402
So. what's the difference now?

289
00:21:04.070 --> 00:21:07.198
The difference is.
he didn't just not tell us.

290
00:21:08.491 --> 00:21:09.784
he lied to us.

291
00:21:10.285 --> 00:21:12.638
It's like when I brought you along
to lectures when you were a kid

292
00:21:12.662 --> 00:21:14.515
and gave you a crayon
and told you to take notes.

293
00:21:16.332 --> 00:21:17.667
He gave us busywork.

294
00:21:18.751 --> 00:21:20.044
I believed in him.

295
00:21:23.673 --> 00:21:24.674
Every word.

296
00:21:28.344 --> 00:21:30.263
And he just pulled the rug
out from under us.

297
00:21:33.099 --> 00:21:35.435
How do you think I feel?

298
00:21:41.900 --> 00:21:43.401
I'm sorry he didn't know you.

299
00:21:45.695 --> 00:21:46.738
Know me.

300
00:21:48.114 --> 00:21:49.324
It's more than that.

301
00:21:51.159 --> 00:21:55.330
All these years
thinking the ghost was talking to me.

302
00:21:57.332 --> 00:21:59.083
I convinced myself it was Hari.

303
00:22:00.084 --> 00:22:06.883
and I started to believe that
I actually was special.

304
00:22:08.509 --> 00:22:10.220
But if the visions
weren't coming from him.

305
00:22:10.303 --> 00:22:12.138
then who were they coming from?

306
00:22:12.931 --> 00:22:15.600
No one? My imagination?

307
00:22:16.267 --> 00:22:18.269
You are special. Salvor.

308
00:22:20.438 --> 00:22:21.522
The null field.

309
00:22:22.398 --> 00:22:25.985
What you did. bringing the <i>Invictus</i>.
it meant everything.

310
00:22:29.322 --> 00:22:30.531
We survived...

311
00:22:32.742 --> 00:22:33.826
against all odds.

312
00:22:34.494 --> 00:22:35.870
You were right.

313
00:22:38.122 --> 00:22:40.083
We have to make our own plan now.

314
00:23:02.689 --> 00:23:05.650
I respected her. in a way.

315
00:23:07.860 --> 00:23:09.320
I'm sorry it came down to this.

316
00:23:10.446 --> 00:23:11.447
I'm not.

317
00:23:12.782 --> 00:23:15.994
No next move. just a last one.
Isn't that what you said about her?

318
00:23:18.288 --> 00:23:20.456
I was just trying to rattle you.

319
00:23:20.540 --> 00:23:22.000
Obviously it worked. Warden.

320
00:23:25.128 --> 00:23:28.715
I wanted the next move for my child.

321
00:23:30.550 --> 00:23:33.928
Over a century ago.
this was offered to the emperor in peace.

322
00:23:37.056 --> 00:23:38.391
I'm offering it again...

323
00:23:41.895 --> 00:23:42.896
to you.

324
00:23:46.274 --> 00:23:49.944
She respected you as well. in a way.

325
00:24:01.873 --> 00:24:04.083
Will you take her back to Anacreon?

326
00:24:04.959 --> 00:24:08.046
No. We've brought Anacreon to her.

327
00:24:08.796 --> 00:24:12.592
The cutting is from a Tallyn oak.
the same wood your bow was carved from.

328
00:24:13.134 --> 00:24:16.679
Our foresters tell me it might be
stubborn enough to take root here.

329
00:24:19.057 --> 00:24:20.350
Would you help me. Warden?

330
00:24:22.101 --> 00:24:23.102
Yeah.

331
00:24:52.257 --> 00:24:53.657
<i>In the months that followed.</i>

332
00:24:53.716 --> 00:24:56.761
<i>the children of the Outer Reach
took Hari's words to heart.</i>

333
00:24:57.345 --> 00:25:00.390
<i>setting aside hatred in favor of strength.</i>

334
00:25:02.684 --> 00:25:08.147
<i>It takes more power to build than to burn.
and Hari wanted them to build.</i>

335
00:25:11.693 --> 00:25:13.069
<i>As for the </i>Invictus<i>.</i>

336
00:25:13.152 --> 00:25:16.656
<i>Hugo Crast. of all people.
became its captain.</i>

337
00:26:07.332 --> 00:26:09.876
<i>He took it to the far side of their star</i>

338
00:26:09.959 --> 00:26:14.964
<i>and generated a mega-flare.
allowing the Foundation to be free.</i>

339
00:26:42.575 --> 00:26:43.785
Captain Crast.

340
00:26:44.369 --> 00:26:45.453
- Poly.
- Warden.

341
00:26:46.246 --> 00:26:47.538
How goes the <i>Invictus?</i>

342
00:26:47.622 --> 00:26:49.457
Oh. we managed to stabilize the drives.

343
00:26:49.540 --> 00:26:52.085
so we won't be jumping
into the heart of a star anytime soon.

344
00:26:52.168 --> 00:26:54.045
And how long before we can build another?

345
00:26:54.128 --> 00:26:55.672
Eighteen months. ma'am.

346
00:26:58.424 --> 00:27:00.802
- You like it up in space. Poly?
- I do.

347
00:27:02.845 --> 00:27:05.139
And. uh.
how long are you dirt-side. Captain?

348
00:27:05.723 --> 00:27:07.225
Fourteen long hours. Warden.

349
00:27:07.308 --> 00:27:08.351
Mmm.

350
00:27:08.434 --> 00:27:11.145
Mirror on my telescope's
a little out of alignment.

351
00:27:11.646 --> 00:27:14.023
Think you could help me recollimate it?

352
00:27:15.149 --> 00:27:16.943
Guys. I know what you're talking about.

353
00:27:18.528 --> 00:27:21.072
Well. then why don't you
politely piss off. Poly?

354
00:29:40.712 --> 00:29:41.713
Stop!

355
00:29:48.803 --> 00:29:50.013
Wait!

356
00:30:36.976 --> 00:30:38.895
If it's not you. then who is it. Hari?

357
00:31:04.128 --> 00:31:05.380
I remember this one.

358
00:31:05.463 --> 00:31:07.715
That was your favorite.

359
00:31:08.967 --> 00:31:10.760
You used to sleep with it in your crib.

360
00:31:11.970 --> 00:31:14.806
If you had a nightmare.
he used to say you could blow it.

361
00:31:16.057 --> 00:31:18.393
and the ghosts would fly away.

362
00:31:20.436 --> 00:31:22.981
Most of the time.
just holding it was enough to soothe you.

363
00:31:23.606 --> 00:31:26.442
Thank goodness. A child with a whistle is
a trial for the soul.

364
00:31:29.028 --> 00:31:31.656
He used to drive me crazy
how often I'd find him out here

365
00:31:31.739 --> 00:31:34.993
having fallen asleep while he was working.

366
00:31:36.286 --> 00:31:38.746
Oh. he was terrible
when he first started making them.

367
00:31:39.247 --> 00:31:43.084
But after a few hundred nights.
Abbas developed a knack for it.

368
00:31:45.920 --> 00:31:49.507
He'd have been proud. you know?
You becoming mayor. filling his shoes.

369
00:31:50.258 --> 00:31:53.845
The election's just a formality.
Everyone knows you'll win by a landslide.

370
00:31:53.928 --> 00:31:57.265
Mom. who's the girl from the water planet?

371
00:32:05.398 --> 00:32:08.026
On the slow ship.
we had a seed bank program.

372
00:32:08.109 --> 00:32:10.778
It wasn't safe bringing the baby to term
in space.

373
00:32:10.862 --> 00:32:16.075
so we banked our eggs and embryos
as insurance against the future.

374
00:32:17.201 --> 00:32:19.537
I chose one from a controversial donor.

375
00:32:22.624 --> 00:32:23.666
Gaal Dornick.

376
00:32:25.043 --> 00:32:26.883
Any change
in your birth directive?

377
00:32:28.588 --> 00:32:30.673
I got to know her a little
before we lost her.

378
00:32:30.757 --> 00:32:32.634
She had a remarkable mind.

379
00:32:33.343 --> 00:32:34.552
And the father?

380
00:32:35.261 --> 00:32:36.721
Raych Foss.

381
00:32:36.804 --> 00:32:38.514
I've seen them both as children.

382
00:32:40.975 --> 00:32:42.018
Gaal tonight.

383
00:32:43.519 --> 00:32:45.271
And. uh. Raych...

384
00:32:47.607 --> 00:32:49.442
at the start of the crisis.

385
00:32:50.109 --> 00:32:51.110
Hey!

386
00:32:51.819 --> 00:32:55.490
All this time I thought
I was living Hari's memories.

387
00:32:56.241 --> 00:32:57.742
But I was actually living theirs.

388
00:32:58.576 --> 00:33:01.246
It makes so much sense now.
why I am so different.

389
00:33:01.329 --> 00:33:05.291
I carried you in my womb. Salvor.
You're still my daughter.

390
00:33:05.375 --> 00:33:08.211
I know. But I am their daughter too.

391
00:33:10.755 --> 00:33:13.132
Gaal escaped in a cryo-pod. Where?

392
00:33:13.758 --> 00:33:15.426
I was still early on in our journey.

393
00:33:15.510 --> 00:33:18.513
It would've been
somewhere along the Orion Spur.

394
00:33:19.430 --> 00:33:21.057
I think she's still out there. Mom.

395
00:33:23.017 --> 00:33:26.479
I think she's
the one who's been reaching out to me.

396
00:33:26.563 --> 00:33:30.024
I think that she is
behind all my instincts.

397
00:33:30.108 --> 00:33:32.026
Hon. that was 40 light-years
from Terminus.

398
00:33:32.110 --> 00:33:33.444
How could that possibly work?

399
00:33:33.528 --> 00:33:34.862
I don't know. but it is her.

400
00:33:34.946 --> 00:33:40.285
And if Gaal was special in some way.
any way. it might explain why I am too.

401
00:33:40.368 --> 00:33:42.579
You've always been drawn to the stars.

402
00:33:42.662 --> 00:33:45.039
Yeah. and now we know why.

403
00:33:46.499 --> 00:33:48.167
'Cause something is tugging at me.

404
00:33:49.586 --> 00:33:51.462
Mom. I have to try and find her.

405
00:33:52.505 --> 00:33:55.008
I know. love.

406
00:33:56.593 --> 00:33:57.677
And I want you to.

407
00:33:59.470 --> 00:34:01.550
Here's the thing though. Mom.
I need to go right now.

408
00:34:02.432 --> 00:34:05.184
I'm worried if I don't go now.
I'll never find the courage again.

409
00:34:11.274 --> 00:34:14.235
Take the ghost whistle.
And something else.

410
00:34:23.077 --> 00:34:25.747
When you find her. give her this.

411
00:34:28.291 --> 00:34:30.084
It was always meant to be hers.

412
00:34:32.629 --> 00:34:36.007
I'm sorry. For everything.

413
00:34:37.550 --> 00:34:39.594
There's nothing to forgive. Mom.

414
00:34:41.471 --> 00:34:43.723
I was exactly where I needed to be.

415
00:35:20.510 --> 00:35:21.594
<i>Beggar</i>. wake up.

416
00:35:32.938 --> 00:35:34.399
Figured I'd find you here.

417
00:35:37.193 --> 00:35:38.194
Damn.

418
00:35:38.778 --> 00:35:40.530
You wanted a clean getaway.

419
00:35:41.114 --> 00:35:42.615
I know you too well. Sal.

420
00:35:44.158 --> 00:35:46.244
Think it was
the kiss on the cheek that did it.

421
00:35:46.327 --> 00:35:50.331
I just didn't want it to hurt
any more than it had to.

422
00:35:51.249 --> 00:35:52.709
It's not love if it doesn't hurt.

423
00:35:54.002 --> 00:35:57.422
I learned that when I had to leave Thespis
so the others could eat.

424
00:35:58.631 --> 00:36:00.383
And no one came chasing after me.

425
00:36:02.260 --> 00:36:03.845
Are you chasing after me. then?

426
00:36:06.139 --> 00:36:07.974
You know. you can come if you want to.

427
00:36:08.641 --> 00:36:10.643
I would if you really wanted me to.

428
00:36:11.895 --> 00:36:14.939
But I get the feeling this is
something you need to do alone.

429
00:36:19.027 --> 00:36:21.738
I always knew you'd let this planet
shrug you off one day.

430
00:36:24.240 --> 00:36:26.534
Just figured I'd be by your side
when it happened.

431
00:36:28.077 --> 00:36:29.245
Will you be mad later?

432
00:36:30.872 --> 00:36:32.206
Never.

433
00:36:53.561 --> 00:36:55.146
Take care of my planet. won't you?

434
00:36:55.897 --> 00:36:57.273
Take care of my ship.

435
00:36:57.357 --> 00:36:59.984
She's not your ship anymore.

436
00:37:01.027 --> 00:37:03.321
It's not my planet.

437
00:37:06.532 --> 00:37:07.992
Galaxy's a big place. Sal.

438
00:37:09.869 --> 00:37:11.537
Any idea where you'll start?

439
00:37:12.205 --> 00:37:13.206
Got a hunch.

440
00:37:15.124 --> 00:37:16.125
Go on. Beat it.

441
00:37:21.839 --> 00:37:22.840
Go.

442
00:37:23.967 --> 00:37:24.968
Go on.

443
00:38:07.051 --> 00:38:08.428
Goodbye. Salvor Hardin.

444
00:39:39.185 --> 00:39:40.186
Empire.

445
00:39:44.524 --> 00:39:45.525
It's time.

446
00:39:48.736 --> 00:39:49.737
You must hate me.

447
00:39:51.489 --> 00:39:53.324
I could never hate you. Empire.

448
00:39:54.325 --> 00:39:55.326
I love you.

449
00:39:56.661 --> 00:39:58.079
Because you're programmed to.

450
00:39:59.163 --> 00:40:02.750
All love is programming.
biological or otherwise.

451
00:40:03.835 --> 00:40:06.462
When a human mother looks
into her newborn's eyes.

452
00:40:07.005 --> 00:40:08.798
their brain waves synchronize.

453
00:40:44.667 --> 00:40:45.668
Empire.

454
00:40:45.752 --> 00:40:48.004
Damn your courtly deportment. boy.

455
00:40:48.963 --> 00:40:50.757
You almost brought us down.

456
00:40:50.840 --> 00:40:52.175
I'm sorry. Brother. I...

457
00:40:52.258 --> 00:40:55.178
You are no brother to me. nor to Cleon I.

458
00:40:55.261 --> 00:40:57.889
nor to any other Cleon
who walked these polished floors.

459
00:40:57.972 --> 00:41:00.266
You are a deformity.

460
00:41:00.350 --> 00:41:03.853
And if I had my way.
you would already be ash.

461
00:41:05.480 --> 00:41:06.856
But as you pointed out.

462
00:41:06.940 --> 00:41:10.401
that is a judgment
for the middle throne to decide.

463
00:41:12.862 --> 00:41:14.197
During my time away.

464
00:41:14.280 --> 00:41:17.659
I had much opportunity
to reflect upon our dynasty.

465
00:41:20.286 --> 00:41:23.206
I went to sleep
in one sector of the galaxy.

466
00:41:23.289 --> 00:41:24.958
then awoke in another.

467
00:41:26.668 --> 00:41:29.587
It's a miracle. by all accounts.

468
00:41:30.922 --> 00:41:33.216
folding space and time.

469
00:41:33.716 --> 00:41:35.802
And then. on the Maiden.

470
00:41:36.594 --> 00:41:39.764
I met pilgrims who had worked
their whole lives

471
00:41:39.847 --> 00:41:41.766
just to walk a spiral of salt.

472
00:41:41.849 --> 00:41:45.478
in the hopes that they might be granted
a vision before they die.

473
00:41:46.896 --> 00:41:47.897
I...

474
00:41:50.942 --> 00:41:54.320
We were challenged by a woman who claimed

475
00:41:54.404 --> 00:41:59.784
that a soul incapable of change is
a soul doomed to stagnation.

476
00:42:01.286 --> 00:42:04.581
I believe Seldon himself implied
something similar.

477
00:42:05.665 --> 00:42:08.585
Seldon was a vainglorious fraud.

478
00:42:08.668 --> 00:42:09.794
And yet. Brother...

479
00:42:10.295 --> 00:42:11.296
And yet...

480
00:42:13.172 --> 00:42:17.468
a bough incapable of bending
will eventually break.

481
00:42:19.679 --> 00:42:22.432
It is time the dynasty bent.

482
00:42:22.974 --> 00:42:24.267
Just a little.

483
00:42:27.520 --> 00:42:28.605
Are you insane?

484
00:42:30.356 --> 00:42:32.025
Did that jump addle your brain?

485
00:42:33.276 --> 00:42:36.446
This is why you should never have left.

486
00:42:37.030 --> 00:42:41.075
Our entire empire is built on
imperishable permanence.

487
00:42:41.159 --> 00:42:43.453
If the Galactic Council discovers

488
00:42:43.536 --> 00:42:46.390
- our dynastic thread is broken...
- Galactic Council? They'd never know.

489
00:42:46.414 --> 00:42:48.416
- ...we are through!
- We could learn from this.

490
00:42:48.499 --> 00:42:51.920
- Perhaps even benefit from a slight...
- Benefit?

491
00:42:52.003 --> 00:42:53.856
- Demerzel.
- How dare you lay your hands on me?

492
00:42:53.880 --> 00:42:56.025
- You've grown weak.
- Please don't let them kill me.

493
00:42:56.049 --> 00:42:57.383
- I won't.
- This is nonsense.

494
00:43:02.347 --> 00:43:06.643
I would rather decant another one of you.
than have that aberration live amongst us.

495
00:43:06.726 --> 00:43:08.478
The decision is mine to make!

496
00:43:08.561 --> 00:43:10.230
Not if it brings about our ruin!

497
00:43:10.313 --> 00:43:12.023
Psychohistory predicted...

498
00:43:12.106 --> 00:43:13.566
Psychohistory?

499
00:43:13.650 --> 00:43:18.655
We are Empire. History bends to us!

500
00:43:19.906 --> 00:43:21.115
No!

501
00:43:29.332 --> 00:43:30.917
I am loyal. Empire.

502
00:43:32.085 --> 00:43:35.046
to the Cleonic Dynasty above all else.

503
00:43:36.047 --> 00:43:37.048
No.

504
00:43:49.352 --> 00:43:51.896
You can dispose
of the body yourself.

505
00:43:55.608 --> 00:44:00.238
I expect another one incarnated
and up to speed by breakfast tomorrow.

506
00:46:26.092 --> 00:46:27.760
What? Speak.

507
00:46:29.554 --> 00:46:32.181
The rebels' plans to undermine the dynasty

508
00:46:33.141 --> 00:46:35.351
appear to be more extensive
than we first believed.

509
00:46:40.273 --> 00:46:43.234
We thought the gene editing was
limited solely to Dawn's person.

510
00:46:43.860 --> 00:46:45.904
that it was done after he was incarnated.

511
00:46:46.654 --> 00:46:48.323
But after more extensive testing.

512
00:46:49.073 --> 00:46:51.200
it seems they've adulterated
the source itself.

513
00:46:52.452 --> 00:46:54.662
Then all replacement clones...

514
00:46:55.496 --> 00:46:57.081
...are no longer pure copies.

515
00:46:58.833 --> 00:47:00.585
When did this happen?

516
00:47:00.668 --> 00:47:02.295
We don't know precisely.

517
00:47:03.713 --> 00:47:09.802
Are you saying that
I. myself. am adulterated?

518
00:47:12.263 --> 00:47:13.264
Possibly.

519
00:47:16.017 --> 00:47:17.018
Yes.

520
00:47:19.062 --> 00:47:20.188
And Dusk?

521
00:47:21.064 --> 00:47:22.982
Empire's being examined as we speak.

522
00:47:26.861 --> 00:47:28.154
Thank you. Shadowmaster.

523
00:47:29.697 --> 00:47:30.698
You may leave.

524
00:50:32.130 --> 00:50:34.549
<i>Entering Synnaxian aerospace.</i>

525
00:50:46.352 --> 00:50:47.854
Initiate reentry.

526
00:50:47.937 --> 00:50:49.689
<i>Secure for reentry.</i>

527
00:51:09.417 --> 00:51:10.835
<i>Climbing from the cradle.</i>

528
00:51:12.795 --> 00:51:14.672
<i>Leaving the comfort of home.</i>

529
00:51:17.216 --> 00:51:18.635
<i>No safe harbor.</i>

530
00:51:20.720 --> 00:51:24.974
86.982.283.

531
00:51:25.058 --> 00:51:29.229
86.982.331...

532
00:51:32.774 --> 00:51:37.028
86.982.341.

533
00:51:41.616 --> 00:51:44.035
<i>Just a cry in the dark.</i>

534
00:51:47.330 --> 00:51:48.331
<i>Are we alone?</i>

535
00:51:59.175 --> 00:52:03.429
<i>And even if we aren't.
will anyone bother to answer?</i>

536
00:52:40.800 --> 00:52:42.010
Okay.

537
00:54:44.173 --> 00:54:45.800
Go away.

538
00:57:29.172 --> 00:57:31.966
Hey. Hey. can you hear me?

539
00:57:33.218 --> 00:57:34.219
Shh.

540
00:57:35.261 --> 00:57:36.387
It's okay.

541
00:57:36.471 --> 00:57:38.598
It's okay. You're okay. Shh. It's okay.

542
00:57:39.432 --> 00:57:41.726
What were you doing down there?

543
00:57:41.809 --> 00:57:44.520
The readout said
you'd been in cryo over a century.

544
00:57:45.855 --> 00:57:47.398
I crash-landed.

545
00:57:48.107 --> 00:57:49.734
I came looking for someone.

546
00:57:51.069 --> 00:57:52.153
Who?

547
00:58:00.370 --> 00:58:01.371
You.

548
00:58:03.623 --> 00:58:04.624
What?

549
00:58:08.795 --> 00:58:12.548
My name is Salvor Hardin.

550
00:58:18.805 --> 00:58:19.931
I'm your daughter.

551
00:58:23.851 --> 00:58:25.603
I'm pretty sure this belongs to you.

552
00:58:43.496 --> 00:58:45.081
<i>Sometimes you leap.</i>

553
00:58:46.916 --> 00:58:50.044
<i>And sometimes. someone catches you.</i>

553
00:58:51.305 --> 00:59:51.941
